{
  "doc_id": "39917",
  "text": "Over the past decade it has become possible to record from much larger numbers of neurons than in the past [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , even though this number is still a mere shadow of the total number of neurons present. The premise behind collecting these large data sets is that it will lead to improvements in correlating neuronal activity with specific sensations, motion, or memory, and possibly including their adaptation and learning [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] .",
